[signal arg="start chapter 2"]
yuna: Two weeks.
yuna: That's how long I've spent in this city —
yuna: — and I still don't fully understand how Baku operates.
yuna: She has no patrol schedule.
yuna: No documentation system.
yuna: No protocol of any kind that I can study and follow.
yuna: What she does have\: instincts that are somehow always right...
yuna: ...and a calmness that makes no sense for someone living alone in a city full of monsters.
yuna: I've tried building a more structured system a few times.
yuna: Baku never refused. She just.... didn't follow it.
yuna: And somehow her way still worked.
[signal arg="start convo"]
[wait time="5.0"]
[signal arg="move"]
[signal arg="yt"]
yuna: Zone C was clear today. But there was activity there yesterday.
[signal arg="bt"]
baku: They moved to B.
[signal arg="yt"]
yuna: How do you know?
[signal arg="bt"]
baku: (points down)
baku: Look at the traces.
[signal arg="out"]
narrator: Yuna looks down. There's something — tracks, or maybe energy residue — she hadn't noticed before.
[signal arg="in"]
[signal arg="yt"]
[wait time="2.0"]
yuna: (pulls out notebook, starts writing)
yuna: Is the pattern consistent?
[signal arg="bt"]
baku: Mostly. They don't like open spaces when the wind comes from the west.
[signal arg="yt"]
yuna: (writing)
yuna: Why didn't you mention this earlier?
[signal arg="bt"]
baku: You didn't ask.
[signal arg="yt"]
yuna: Baku. If there's relevant information —
[signal arg="bt"]
baku: You'll understand it better if you see it yourself. It sticks more that way.
[signal arg="out"]
[wait time="2.0"]
narrator: Yuna closes her notebook. Looks out over the city.
yuna: At the association, everything gets documented. There's a protocol for —
baku: Are you still at the association?
yuna: ......
yuna: ...not yet.
yuna: But I'm going back.
[signal arg="in"]
[signal arg="bt"]
[wait time="1.0"]
baku: (nods)
baku: Okay.
[signal arg="yt"]
yuna: That's all you have to say?
[signal arg="bt"]
baku: Eh?-
label act 2
baku: What do you want me to say?
